<h2><a href="/2008/05/02/my.father.is.visiting" title="Permanent link to this item">My father is visiting</a></h2>

<h3><span class="outleft">2 May 2008, 3pm</span></h3>

<p>Eleven random biographical notes:</p>
<ol>
<li>When I was very small he worked two jobs at once; one was in a sawmill</li>
<li>On his fortieth birthday he got a perm</li>
<li>He used to drink too much, then one day he just stopped</li>
<li>He can be stubborn as a mule who’s just graduated stubborn school</li>
<li>Though born in Alberta, his veins practically pulse with sea water</li>
<li>On a hot day out in a boat near North Pender Island, he dared me to dive into the water to cool off; a week later I developed pneumonia</li>
<li>When she had decided their marriage was over, I helped move out my mother’s stuff while he, completely unaware, was out fishing</li>
<li>His own father was seriously injured when a drunk woman, unable to find her chauffeur, plowed her car through the crowd at Lansdowne Racetrack</li>
<li>We got into a fistfight when I was sixteen and he had me down in seconds</li>
<li>He has a new hearing aid, and a new hip</li>
<li>He is sixty nine years old</li>
</ol>
